<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 17 at 3:38AM EST  by NWS Binghamton</headline>
<description>...WINTRY MIX OF SNOW, SLEET AND FREEZING RAIN THROUGH 6 AM...
Current radar and observations show moderate snow and sleet
across the area. Some freezing rain or even plain rain may begin
to mix in across the valley locations after 4 AM. Snowfall rates
will be up to 1 inch per hour, but lowering as more mixed precipitation
occurs.
Use caution if your must travel early this morning and be prepared
for the winter travel conditions. Untreated roads will be snow
packed, snow covered and icy.</description>
